
@startuml FE08_ListStationFloodConditions_Updated
title FE08 - List Station Flood Conditions (Updated)

actor User
participant UI
participant StationFloodConditionsEndpoint
participant MediatR
participant StationFloodConditionsHandler
participant ExternalRepo
participant ExternalService
database Database

User -> UI: 1. Open "Stations Flood Conditions" screen
UI -> StationFloodConditionsEndpoint: 2. GET /api/v1/stations/conditions
StationFloodConditionsEndpoint -> MediatR: 3. Send(StationFloodConditionsRequest)
MediatR -> StationFloodConditionsHandler: 4. Handle(request)

StationFloodConditionsHandler -> ExternalRepo: 5. GetStations(bounds, status)
ExternalRepo -> Database: 6. SELECT stations WHERE in bounds AND status
Database --> ExternalRepo: 7. Station list
ExternalRepo --> StationFloodConditionsHandler: 8. Stations

StationFloodConditionsHandler -> ExternalRepo: 9. GetLatestWaterLevels(stationIds)
ExternalRepo -> Database: 10. SELECT latest readings per station
Database --> ExternalRepo: 11. Water levels
ExternalRepo --> StationFloodConditionsHandler: 12. Water levels

StationFloodConditionsHandler -> ExternalService: 13. ComputeSeverity(stations, levels)
ExternalService --> StationFloodConditionsHandler: 14. Severity results

StationFloodConditionsHandler -> StationFloodConditionsHandler: 15. Build StationFloodConditionDto list

alt [No stations found]
    StationFloodConditionsHandler --> MediatR: 16. Response { success: true, total: 0, items: [] }
else [Stations found]
    StationFloodConditionsHandler --> MediatR: 17. Response { success: true, total > 0, items }
end

MediatR --> StationFloodConditionsEndpoint: 18. Response
StationFloodConditionsEndpoint --> UI: 19. HTTP 200 + JSON
UI --> User: 20. Show markers and list

@enduml



@startuml FE08_StationFloodConditionDetail_Updated
title FE08 - Station Flood Condition Detail (Updated)

actor User
participant UI
participant StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint
participant MediatR
participant StationFloodConditionDetailHandler
participant ExternalRepo
participant ExternalService
database Database

User -> UI: 1. Tap on station marker
UI -> StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint: 2. GET /api/v1/stations/{id}/condition
StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint -> MediatR: 3. Send(StationFloodConditionDetailRequest)
MediatR -> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 4. Handle(request)

StationFloodConditionDetailHandler -> ExternalRepo: 5. GetStationById(stationId)
ExternalRepo -> Database: 6. SELECT station WHERE id = stationId
Database --> ExternalRepo: 7. Station or null
ExternalRepo --> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 8. Station or null

alt [Station not found]
    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler --> MediatR: 9. Response { success: false, statusCode: 404 }
    MediatR --> StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint: 10. Error response
    StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint --> UI: 11. 404 Not Found
    UI --> User: 12. Show "Station not found"
else [Station found]
    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler -> ExternalRepo: 13. GetRecentWaterLevels(stationId)
    ExternalRepo -> Database: 14. SELECT latest N readings
    Database --> ExternalRepo: 15. Readings
    ExternalRepo --> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 16. Readings

    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler -> ExternalRepo: 17. GetLatestAlertForStation(stationId)
    ExternalRepo -> Database: 18. SELECT last alert
    Database --> ExternalRepo: 19. Alert (optional)
    ExternalRepo --> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 20. Alert (optional)

    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler -> ExternalService: 21. ComputeSeverity(station, readings, alert)
    ExternalService --> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 22. Severity result

    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler -> StationFloodConditionDetailHandler: 23. Build StationFloodConditionDetailDto

    StationFloodConditionDetailHandler --> MediatR: 24. Response { success: true, data }
    MediatR --> StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint: 25. Success response
    StationFloodConditionDetailEndpoint --> UI: 26. 200 OK + JSON payload
    UI --> User: 27. Show station detail popup
end

@enduml


